28
00:02:30,672 --> 00:02:32,239
You got it!

29
00:02:35,503 --> 00:02:36,286
Hi, Danny.

30
00:02:36,330 --> 00:02:37,679
Hi, Beth.

31
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,119
Morning, Danny.

32
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,468
Hi, John.

33
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,692
Gentlemen, and lady,

34
00:02:50,735 --> 00:02:53,303
I present Manifest Wind,

35
00:02:53,347 --> 00:02:55,087
the pride of our

36
00:02:55,131 --> 00:02:56,828
three-year-olds.

37
00:02:56,872 --> 00:02:59,353
[murmuring]

38
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:01,920
Can we get one with y'all

39
00:03:01,964 --> 00:03:02,834
and Manifest Wind?

40
00:03:02,878 --> 00:03:04,358
Certainly.

41
00:03:06,925 --> 00:03:07,839
See?

42
00:03:07,883 --> 00:03:10,059
Right there.

43
00:03:10,102 --> 00:03:11,365
I want to thank all of you

44
00:03:11,408 --> 00:03:12,801
for coming out, and we will

45
00:03:12,844 --> 00:03:13,758
see you this afternoon at

46
00:03:13,802 --> 00:03:14,629
the races.

47
00:03:14,672 --> 00:03:15,586
Mrs. Slauson, could he be

48
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:16,239
a contender for the

49
00:03:16,283 --> 00:03:16,979
Tucker Stakes?

50
00:03:17,022 --> 00:03:18,502
We'll see.

51
00:03:18,546 --> 00:03:19,808
Harland, is he ready?

52
00:03:19,851 --> 00:03:21,331
And I mean really ready.

53
00:03:21,375 --> 00:03:23,028
I can't afford mistakes

54
00:03:23,072 --> 00:03:24,029
this season.

55
00:03:24,073 --> 00:03:25,248
Mrs. Slauson, I would stake

56
00:03:25,292 --> 00:03:26,597
my career on it.

57
00:03:26,641 --> 00:03:28,425
Oh, Harland, let's hope

58
00:03:28,469 --> 00:03:30,079
it doesn't come to that.

59
00:03:30,122 --> 00:03:31,211
See you in the paddock

60
00:03:31,254 --> 00:03:32,864
this afternoon.

61
00:03:37,695 --> 00:03:39,697
[engine starts, revs]

62
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,621
So, how's he doing, Charlie?

63
00:03:50,665 --> 00:03:52,232
He's still pretty swollen.

64
00:03:53,494 --> 00:03:54,495
Hey, Eddie.

65
00:03:54,538 --> 00:03:55,322
Hey, Danny.

66
00:03:55,365 --> 00:03:56,279
Not off to school yet?

67
00:03:56,323 --> 00:03:57,454
I'm getting there.

68
00:03:57,498 --> 00:03:58,977
Gotta see Mooney first.

69
00:03:59,021 --> 00:04:00,283
Can't that guy do his own

70
00:04:00,327 --> 00:04:02,372
spying around the track?

